<div class="hero"><div class="hero-inner">
<div class="badge"><span class="badge-dot"></span>Honest 2026 comparison</div>
<h1 class="hero-h">ChatGPT Plus vs ChatGPT Team: <em>which one for your team.</em></h1>
<p class="hero-sub">Plus is the individual plan; Team adds shared workspace features, admin controls, and stronger data terms. The right time to move is usually two or three engaged users, not one.</p>
<div class="verdict"><div class="verdict-l">Short answer</div><p class="verdict-p">Use Plus for solo or very early use. Move to Team once two or three users are getting real value and you want shared workspace, admin controls, and better default data terms. Move to Enterprise when SSO, audit, or custom data agreements become requirements.</p></div>
<p class="note">Pricing references are as of June 2026 and may change. Always verify on each vendor's site before committing.</p>
</div></div>

<section><div class="sec-inner">
<h2 class="h2">ChatGPT Plus: where it wins</h2>
<p class="body">Plus is OpenAI's individual subscription. Frontier model access, GPTs, Projects, and a healthy usage envelope, all on a personal account.</p>
<ul class="ul">
<li><strong>Cheapest entry to frontier ChatGPT.</strong> Lowest barrier for a single user to try paid features.</li>
<li><strong>Personal account.</strong> Useful for individuals and side work that is not company business.</li>
<li><strong>Full feature set.</strong> Custom GPTs, Projects, voice, image generation, advanced reasoning models.</li>
</ul>
</div></section>

<section><div class="sec-inner">
<h2 class="h2">ChatGPT Team: where it wins</h2>
<p class="body">Team is OpenAI's small-organization plan. Shared workspace, admin controls, higher usage envelope, and a default data-handling commitment that does not train on your inputs.</p>
<ul class="ul">
<li><strong>Default no-training data terms.</strong> Inputs are not used to train OpenAI models, by default.</li>
<li><strong>Shared workspace and GPTs.</strong> Team-shared custom GPTs and Projects.</li>
<li><strong>Admin controls.</strong> Add and remove users, manage billing centrally.</li>
<li><strong>Higher usage envelope.</strong> More headroom for power users.</li>
</ul>
</div></section>

<section><div class="sec-inner">
<h2 class="h2">Side-by-side</h2>
<p class="body">A direct, dimension-by-dimension look. Use this as a quick scan, then read the decision framework below.</p>
<table class="cmp-table">
<thead><tr><th>Dimension</th><th>ChatGPT Plus</th><th>ChatGPT Team</th></tr></thead>
<tbody>
<tr><td>For</td><td>One person</td><td>A small organization</td></tr>
<tr><td>Default data terms</td><td>Personal-account terms</td><td>No training on your data</td></tr>
<tr><td>Shared workspace</td><td>No</td><td>Yes</td></tr>
<tr><td>Admin controls</td><td>No</td><td>Yes</td></tr>
<tr><td>Pricing model</td><td>Per-month personal</td><td>Per-seat-per-month with minimum</td></tr>
<tr><td>SSO and audit</td><td>No</td><td>No (Enterprise)</td></tr>
<tr><td>Sweet spot</td><td>Individual use</td><td>2 to 150-ish users</td></tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div></section>

<section><div class="sec-inner">
<h2 class="h2">When to choose ChatGPT Plus</h2>
<ul class="ul">
<li>You are a solo user trying paid ChatGPT.</li>
<li>Your AI use is personal or side projects, not company business.</li>
<li>You are not ready to pay for a full team yet.</li>
</ul>
</div></section>

<section><div class="sec-inner">
<h2 class="h2">When to choose ChatGPT Team</h2>
<ul class="ul">
<li>You have two or more engaged users at the same company.</li>
<li>You want default no-training data terms for company use.</li>
<li>You want shared GPTs, projects, and central billing.</li>
<li>You are not yet at the size that needs SSO and Enterprise compliance.</li>
</ul>
</div></section>

<section><div class="sec-inner">
<h2 class="h2">When most teams should run both</h2>
<p class="body">Most organizations standardize on Team or Enterprise and stop using personal Plus accounts for company work. Mixing creates data-handling and billing issues you do not want.</p>
<ul class="ul">
<li>During a trial period where new users start on Plus.</li>
<li>When individuals want a personal subscription on top of the company plan for personal projects.</li>
<li>Almost never as a long-term arrangement for company work.</li>
</ul>
<p class="body">Combined seat cost is small relative to the productivity lift from picking the right tool for each job. The wrong move is buying one because it is cheaper and forcing it into work it is not built for.</p>
</div></section>

<section><div class="sec-inner">
<h2 class="h2">Frequently asked questions</h2>
<div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">When should I upgrade from Plus to Team?</div><div class="faq-a">When you have two or three engaged users at the same company, or when you want default no-training data terms for company-owned work.</div></div>
<div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">What does Team actually add over Plus?</div><div class="faq-a">Shared workspace, team-shared GPTs and Projects, admin controls, central billing, higher usage envelope, and no-training default data terms.</div></div>
<div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">Should we go straight to Enterprise?</div><div class="faq-a">Only if SSO, audit logs, dedicated support, or custom data agreements are real requirements. Most teams under 50 users get more value from Team.</div></div>
<div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">How does Team compare to Claude Team?</div><div class="faq-a">Both vendors offer a small-business team tier with shared workspace, admin, and no-training defaults. As of June 2026 they are in similar per-seat ranges. The right pick depends on which assistant your team prefers.</div></div>
<div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">What is the minimum Team seat count?</div><div class="faq-a">Team plans have a minimum seat requirement that changes over time. Verify the current minimum on OpenAI's site before signing up.</div></div>
</div></section>

